01:03:29,360 --> 01:03:31,351
We are The Four Horsemen.

1301
01:03:31,840 --> 01:03:32,910
Good night.

1302
01:03:45,160 --> 01:03:46,514
Get 'em off me!

1303
01:03:47,280 --> 01:03:48,873
Get off! Get off me!

1304
01:03:59,200 --> 01:04:00,599
Get off me!

1305
01:04:09,000 --> 01:04:11,196
All right. I want everyone
on the street! Everyone!

1306
01:04:17,920 --> 01:04:19,877
- Quarterback!
- Quarterback!

1307
01:04:21,360 --> 01:04:22,839
Fuller, meet me in front of the theater

1308
01:04:22,960 --> 01:04:24,519
and bring the tracker.

1309
01:04:24,600 --> 01:04:26,989
Let's go! Let's go! Now! Come on! Let's go!

1310
01:04:27,080 --> 01:04:28,195
Give me the tracker.

1311
01:04:28,640 --> 01:04:29,630
Let's go.

1312
01:04:33,800 --> 01:04:35,074
FBI! Clear!

1313
01:04:35,800 --> 01:04:36,949
- Dylan!
- Damn.

1314
01:04:37,040 --> 01:04:38,030
What have you got?

1315
01:04:38,120 --> 01:04:39,633
That's him right there. Follow the red dot.

1316
01:04:39,720 --> 01:04:42,758
All right, I'll take this.
Go. Box 'em. Cut 'em off that way.

1317
01:04:44,720 --> 01:04:46,233
He's turning left on Burgundy.

1318
01:05:22,960 --> 01:05:24,519
Hey! Move!

1319
01:05:24,600 --> 01:05:25,920
Move! Move!

1320
01:05:28,600 --> 01:05:30,318
I got him heading north on Bourbon.

1321
01:05:30,400 --> 01:05:32,277
- Sorry. Move, move!
- Hey!

1322
01:05:32,360 --> 01:05:34,351
Hey, excuse me. Move, move! Excuse me.

1323
01:05:45,800 --> 01:05:47,473
I've lost him at Bourbon.

1324
01:05:52,880 --> 01:05:54,871
Damn! Where are you?

1325
01:06:06,840 --> 01:06:08,035
Excuse me.

1326
01:06:14,120 --> 01:06:16,111
He's heading south on Exchange Place.

1327
01:06:18,520 --> 01:06:19,555
Stop!

1328
01:06:26,560 --> 01:06:27,914
What are you doing?

1329
01:06:31,360 --> 01:06:33,476
He's going in Napoleon House.

1330
01:06:35,520 --> 01:06:37,079
Move! Move!

1331
01:06:37,960 --> 01:06:39,473
Move out of the way!

1332
01:06:40,200 --> 01:06:41,190
Hey!

1333
01:06:42,040 --> 01:06:43,030
Move!

1334
01:06:45,360 --> 01:06:47,636
He's in the bathroom.
I have him in the bathroom.

1335
01:06:47,760 --> 01:06:50,036
No! No! No!

1336
01:06:51,920 --> 01:06:53,069
Freeze!

1337
01:06:53,920 --> 01:06:55,194
Lower your weapons!

1338
01:06:55,480 --> 01:06:56,550
What?

1339
01:06:56,800 --> 01:06:58,791
I'm tracking myself!

1340
01:06:59,320 --> 01:07:01,277
The Horsemen
left egg on the face of what they call

1341
01:07:01,360 --> 01:07:02,998
the alphabet agencies,

1342
01:07:03,120 --> 01:07:04,269
calling into question

1343
01:07:04,400 --> 01:07:06,630
the efficacy of the FBI's task force

1344
01:07:06,760 --> 01:07:09,479
as well as the man in charge
of the investigation,

1345
01:07:09,560 --> 01:07:11,039
Special Agent Dylan Rhodes,

1346
01:07:11,120 --> 01:07:12,758
who was publicly ridiculed,

1347
01:07:12,880 --> 01:07:15,759
and even tackled at tonight's performance.

1348
01:07:16,120 --> 01:07:17,349
Talk about a fumble.

1349
01:07:17,440 --> 01:07:19,272
This is quickly becoming a national story,

1350
01:07:19,560 --> 01:07:22,359
as The Horsemen have now
seemingly pulled off the impossible

1351
01:07:22,600 --> 01:07:24,876
for the second time in as many days.

1352
01:07:25,120 --> 01:07:26,838
Two nights ago in Vegas, The Horsemen

1353
01:07:26,960 --> 01:07:28,314
seemingly robbed a bank in Paris...

1354
01:07:28,640 --> 01:07:29,789
Hey.

1355
01:07:30,960 --> 01:07:32,075
What are you doing?

1356
01:07:32,160 --> 01:07:33,559
I'm having a drink.

1357
01:07:36,640 --> 01:07:37,994
I came to get you.

1358
01:07:38,600 --> 01:07:39,795
I'm worried about you.

1359
01:07:39,960 --> 01:07:41,473
You're worried about me.
Well, I'm worried about you.

1360
01:07:41,600 --> 01:07:42,715
Atlas. You had him.

1361
01:07:42,800 --> 01:07:44,074
He didn't have a weapon.

1362
01:07:44,160 --> 01:07:45,639
I couldn't shoot him and you know that.

1363
01:07:45,760 --> 01:07:48,593
Yeah, but you... You let him go.

1364
01:07:48,760 --> 01:07:49,989
Didn't you?

1365
01:07:50,560 --> 01:07:52,233
A pretty French girl
shows up out of the blue,

1366
01:07:52,320 --> 01:07:54,038
acts like she's my partner
and then she lets the bad guy go?

1367
01:07:54,120 --> 01:07:55,235
Let go of my arm.

1368
01:07:55,320 --> 01:07:56,993
Who exactly are you anyway?

1369
01:07:59,160 --> 01:08:01,151
I thought you said you were a desk agent.

1370
01:08:06,200 --> 01:08:07,429
Not bad.

1371
01:08:09,360 --> 01:08:10,350
What is this?

1372
01:08:13,400 --> 01:08:14,834
What's the Eye of Horus?

1373
01:08:15,000 --> 01:08:17,992
Certainly nothing
I want to get into tonight.

1374
01:08:18,120 --> 01:08:20,680
You're dismissive enough
about me when you're sober.

1375
01:08:21,200 --> 01:08:23,350
Find your way back yourself.

1376
01:08:27,360 --> 01:08:30,512
Mr. Bradley? Mr. Tressler would like you
to join him for a drink.

1377
01:08:39,960 --> 01:08:40,995
Sir.

1378
01:08:41,200 --> 01:08:42,429
Thank you.

1379
01:08:43,840 --> 01:08:46,036
What is your role with them?

1380
01:08:46,200 --> 01:08:47,190
Role?

1381
01:08:47,400 --> 01:08:49,118
Yes. You seem to know
everything about them.

1382
01:08:49,200 --> 01:08:50,998
What they're gonna do.
Where they're gonna be.

1383
01:08:51,200 --> 01:08:52,873
If it makes you feel any better,

1384
01:08:53,000 --> 01:08:54,195
this wasn't about you.

1385
01:08:54,280 --> 01:08:57,750
Please tell me why this was not about me.

1386
01:08:58,520 --> 01:09:01,080
This is a magic trick, Mr. Tressler.

1387
01:09:01,360 --> 01:09:03,670
Played out on a global scale.

1388
01:09:04,040 --> 01:09:07,999
You, sir, are the abracadabra.

1389
01:09:08,560 --> 01:09:11,359
The distraction, while they
set up the real trick.

1390
01:09:11,560 --> 01:09:15,713
I was a $140-million distraction?

1391
01:09:16,560 --> 01:09:17,709
Yes.

1392
01:09:18,400 --> 01:09:22,553
And that very ego that got you involved
with them in the first place

1393
01:09:23,040 --> 01:09:24,553
is what keeps you from seeing that.

1394
01:09:24,720 --> 01:09:26,233
- You know...
- "I can destroy you."

1395
01:09:26,360 --> 01:09:27,759
Yes, I do know.

1396
01:09:27,960 --> 01:09:29,234
Well, you won't.

1397
01:09:29,800 --> 01:09:31,950
And you won't destroy them.

1398
01:09:32,080 --> 01:09:34,117
Whatever this grand trick is,

1399
01:09:34,440 --> 01:09:37,193
it was designed a long time ago.

1400
01:09:37,440 --> 01:09:41,957
And I believe that what's about to follow
is really going to amaze.

1401
01:09:42,800 --> 01:09:47,351
So I suggest
you sit back and enjoy your front row seat.

1402
01:09:47,800 --> 01:09:50,474
You paid quite a lot of good money for it.

1403
01:09:50,680 --> 01:09:52,717
Whatever you stand to make

1404
01:09:54,840 --> 01:09:58,390
I'll double it, if you expose them now.

1405
01:09:58,600 --> 01:09:59,999
And destroy them.

1406
01:10:00,400 --> 01:10:02,391
I stand to make five million.

1407
01:10:03,120 --> 01:10:04,349
Am I flinching?

1408
01:10:06,480 --> 01:10:08,073
No, you're not.

1409
01:11:28,880 --> 01:11:29,995
Hey.

1410
01:11:31,360 --> 01:11:33,590
I'm sorry for your arm.

1411
01:11:33,680 --> 01:11:35,239
No. I'm sorry.

1412
01:11:35,320 --> 01:11:37,596
I was an asshole. I was drunk.

1413
01:11:39,560 --> 01:11:42,154
I'm at a loss.

1414
01:11:44,080 --> 01:11:49,473
You know, when Merritt said I hardly spent
any time away from the desk, he was right.

1415
01:11:49,560 --> 01:11:52,837
I'm a researcher. That's what I do best.

1416
01:11:53,960 --> 01:11:57,840
So what's this all about?

1417
01:11:58,560 --> 01:12:01,234
Supposedly, if you buy into it,

1418
01:12:01,320 --> 01:12:02,674
The Eye are the keepers

1419
01:12:02,760 --> 01:12:03,955
of real magic

1420
01:12:04,040 --> 01:12:06,953
and the protectors of those who practice it.

1421
01:12:07,040 --> 01:12:08,951
"Candidates for initiations

1422
01:12:09,040 --> 01:12:12,192
"must follow a series of commands
with blind obedience."

1423
01:12:13,200 --> 01:12:16,397
- This isn't real.
- But there are some who think it is.

1424
01:12:16,880 --> 01:12:18,393
May I?

1425
01:12:20,200 --> 01:12:24,512
According to this,
they only take new people twice a century.

1426
01:12:24,600 --> 01:12:27,991
So what? The Horsemen are doing
these shows in order to get into this thing?

1427
01:12:28,080 --> 01:12:29,309
- I don't know.
- I don't know.

1428
01:12:29,400 --> 01:12:34,395
I mean, I guess these guys
could just rob banks to rob banks.

1429
01:12:34,480 --> 01:12:36,790
They don't have to put on a show for that.

1430
01:12:36,880 --> 01:12:38,393
It's probably just a myth.

1431
01:12:38,480 --> 01:12:42,599
But it doesn't make any sense,
and I don't think logic will solve this for us.

1432
01:12:42,680 --> 01:12:45,274
- You don't say?
- No.

1433
01:12:46,520 --> 01:12:51,151
I believe
that some things are only discovered

1434
01:12:51,240 --> 01:12:55,632
if you take certain leaps.

1435
01:13:02,640 --> 01:13:05,758
- Well, I gotta get to...
- Yeah. Yeah.

1436
01:13:05,840 --> 01:13:07,990
- Thanks. Good night.
- Yeah. Good night.

1437
01:13:08,080 --> 01:13:09,878
- Sorry.
- It's all right.

1438
01:13:12,400 --> 01:13:15,836
If The Eye did exist, we'd have to assume
they were watching us, right?

1439
01:13:15,920 --> 01:13:17,194
Shit.

1440
01:13:17,280 --> 01:13:19,874
I think someone is watching us,
but it isn't magic.

1441
01:13:19,960 --> 01:13:22,952
Your fears are correct.
This is not and has never been your phone.

1442
01:13:23,040 --> 01:13:27,716
It's a clone in every way, except for this.

1443
01:13:27,840 --> 01:13:29,114
A bug.

1444
01:13:29,200 --> 01:13:33,034
Someone has
heard every call, read every text.

1445
01:13:33,280 --> 01:13:34,475
That's how
they were able to stay ahead of us.

1446
01:13:34,600 --> 01:13:35,431
God damn it!

1447
01:13:36,800 --> 01:13:38,598
Get me Atlas' interrogation tape.

1448
01:13:38,920 --> 01:13:40,433
Yes, sir. I have it on the hard drive.

1449
01:13:42,280 --> 01:13:43,350
Picture's up.

1450
01:13:43,840 --> 01:13:45,592
Okay, fast forward.

1451
01:13:45,960 --> 01:13:47,439
Go on, go on. Freeze!

1452
01:13:48,200 --> 01:13:49,998
Okay. Frame by frame. Go on.

1453
01:13:50,880 --> 01:13:51,915
Play it through.

1454
01:13:53,040 --> 01:13:55,350
Stop. Zoom in tighter. Tighter.

1455
01:13:55,800 --> 01:13:57,598
There. That's where he took my phone.

1456
01:13:58,880 --> 01:14:00,075
Is that thing transmitting?

1457
01:14:00,240 --> 01:14:01,639
Only when
you're making a call or sending a text.

1458
01:14:01,840 --> 01:14:02,796
Plus I removed the bug.

1459
01:14:02,880 --> 01:14:04,439
All right. Put it back in
and turn on the phone.

1460
01:14:04,680 --> 01:14:06,478
They don't know
that we know about the bug.

1461
01:14:06,680 --> 01:14:08,671
As of this instant, we are ahead of them.

1462
01:14:08,760 --> 01:14:10,910
We need to keep it that way. Understand?

1463
01:14:11,320 --> 01:14:12,640
Find my real phone and track it.

1464
01:14:12,760 --> 01:14:16,071
Already did. As of about 20 minutes ago,
it's in New York City.

1465
01:14:16,280 --> 01:14:17,315
Good.

1466
01:14:17,720 --> 01:14:19,393
I wanna cut 'em off at the knees.

1467
01:14:19,480 --> 01:14:20,595
They got power? Cut it.

1468
01:14:20,800 --> 01:14:24,077
They got phones, electricity, water? Cut it.

1469
01:14:24,280 --> 01:14:25,315
Squeeze 'em out.

1470
01:14:25,400 --> 01:14:27,152
I want 'em to feel our presence.

1471
01:14:27,240 --> 01:14:28,753
And get me an airplane!

1472
01:14:31,520 --> 01:14:33,352
The firewall's down.
Do they know about this?

1473
01:14:33,440 --> 01:14:34,396
They who?

1474
01:14:34,480 --> 01:14:36,278
"They," "them," whoever we're working for.

1475
01:14:36,480 --> 01:14:37,629
Who are we working for?

1476
01:14:37,760 --> 01:14:39,831
And are we prepared to go to jail for them?

1477
01:14:39,920 --> 01:14:40,910
Stop being paranoid.

1478
01:14:41,160 --> 01:14:42,230
It really does happen.

1479
01:14:42,440 --> 01:14:44,033
It happened to you.
Doesn't mean it's gonna happen to us.

1480
01:14:44,160 --> 01:14:45,719
Guys, I don't know if can do this, all right.

1481
01:14:45,800 --> 01:14:47,120
I don't want to go to jail, you know?

1482
01:14:47,200 --> 01:14:48,998
Then don't screw up.
You're always talking about

1483
01:14:49,080 --> 01:14:50,275
wanting to be treated like an adult.

1484
01:14:50,360 --> 01:14:51,509
Now might be a good time
to start acting like one.

1485
01:14:51,600 --> 01:14:53,796
Stick to the plan. Stay here and burn it all.

1486
01:15:06,880 --> 01:15:08,075
I don't know what I'm doing here.

1487
01:15:08,280 --> 01:15:09,236
I don't know
what you would do anywhere else.

1488
01:15:09,320 --> 01:15:11,789
I'm here for the pot of gold
at the end of the rainbow.

1489
01:15:12,120 --> 01:15:14,270
That's it. Then I'm gone.

1490
01:15:14,360 --> 01:15:16,510
You can do whatever you want
when this is over, Merritt.

1491
01:15:16,720 --> 01:15:18,836
But until then, you stick to the plan.

1492
01:15:18,920 --> 01:15:20,957
Hey, guys. They're here.

1493
01:15:22,800 --> 01:15:24,791
- My guys are ready to go.
- Let's do this quickly...

1494
01:15:24,880 --> 01:15:26,200
- No.
- What?

1495
01:15:26,280 --> 01:15:27,475
She doesn't have jurisdiction here.

1496
01:15:27,720 --> 01:15:28,994
She's Interpol. She's with me.

1497
01:15:29,080 --> 01:15:30,070
She stays.

1498
01:15:30,160 --> 01:15:31,434
What? What?

1499
01:15:31,520 --> 01:15:32,510
Stay in the car.

1500
01:15:34,800 --> 01:15:35,995
Let's go.

1501
01:15:41,640 --> 01:15:42,675
Okay. Let's do it.

1502
01:15:47,120 --> 01:15:48,110
FBI!

1503
01:15:52,400 --> 01:15:53,720
Ladies first.

1504
01:15:54,320 --> 01:15:55,515
Don't move!

1505
01:16:01,560 --> 01:16:02,994
Tell me.

1506
01:16:03,120 --> 01:16:04,838
Is my money being well-spent?

1507
01:16:05,360 --> 01:16:07,271
Exceedingly well.

1508
01:16:09,040 --> 01:16:10,519
Now you tell me,

1509
01:16:11,320 --> 01:16:12,993
how do you like your Horsemen?

1510
01:16:13,160 --> 01:16:15,197
Fricasseed or fried?

1511
01:16:15,440 --> 01:16:16,475
Shredded.

1512
01:16:17,560 --> 01:16:19,039
I'll tell the chef.

1513
01:17:34,600 --> 01:17:35,590
Freeze!

1514
01:17:42,800 --> 01:17:43,790
Dylan!

1515
01:17:44,760 --> 01:17:45,909
Hold on!

1516
01:17:48,240 --> 01:17:49,275
You little...

1517
01:17:53,800 --> 01:17:54,790
Come here!

1518
01:17:56,560 --> 01:17:58,471
Five is clear. Standing by for six.

1519
01:17:58,680 --> 01:18:00,910
You little shit!

1520
01:18:01,000 --> 01:18:03,230
- What game are you playing?
- What game are you playing?

1521
01:18:03,560 --> 01:18:05,597
We're all good at six. Move to seven.

1522
01:18:05,680 --> 01:18:07,717
Copy that. Going to seven. Go, go, go!

1523
01:18:08,400 --> 01:18:10,391
No, no, no, no, no. Go back!

1524
01:18:10,960 --> 01:18:12,109
Hey!

1525
01:18:13,840 --> 01:18:15,069
Come here!

1526
01:18:46,080 --> 01:18:47,229
Come here!

1527
01:18:47,320 --> 01:18:48,993
All right, hold on, hold on!

1528
01:18:50,920 --> 01:18:52,752
- Really?
- Yup.

1529
01:18:56,960 --> 01:18:57,950
You...

1530
01:19:01,760 --> 01:19:03,239
You little...

1531
01:19:19,280 --> 01:19:20,315
Shit!

1532
01:19:38,720 --> 01:19:39,755
Shit!

1533
01:19:41,160 --> 01:19:42,514
Give me that!

1534
01:20:08,520 --> 01:20:10,477
All units, cover the north exit now!

1535
01:20:10,560 --> 01:20:11,834
Clear on Evan.

1536
01:20:11,920 --> 01:20:13,752
Block every possible exit.

1537
01:20:13,840 --> 01:20:15,353
Hey! Get back. Shit.

1538
01:20:16,840 --> 01:20:18,990
- FBI. Sort of. I need your car. Thanks.
- What?

1539
01:20:19,080 --> 01:20:20,070
What?

1540
01:20:22,200 --> 01:20:23,793
Stop! Stop!

1541
01:20:39,960 --> 01:20:40,995
Hey!

1542
01:21:10,840 --> 01:21:11,750
Good. Follow him!

1543
01:21:11,880 --> 01:21:13,917
Don't ever tell me to stay in the car. Ever.

1544
01:21:14,000 --> 01:21:15,320
I didn't have tactical command.

1545
01:21:15,400 --> 01:21:17,789
If you don't trust me, just tell me.

1546
01:21:17,880 --> 01:21:19,439
Promise me, next time, you will back me up.

1547
01:21:19,560 --> 01:21:21,597
Could we have
this conversation later, please?

1548
01:21:21,680 --> 01:21:23,239
No!

1549
01:21:23,320 --> 01:21:25,596
Okay, fine, I promise. Now, go!

1550
01:21:33,040 --> 01:21:35,554
- Where'd they go?
- Where are they?

1551
01:21:35,640 --> 01:21:37,313
I don't know. She just took some guy's car.

1552
01:21:37,400 --> 01:21:38,834
- Where are they?
- That way. That way.

1553
01:21:38,920 --> 01:21:39,955
- Is that your car?
- Yeah.

1554
01:21:40,080 --> 01:21:41,514
Let's go.

1555
01:22:07,120 --> 01:22:08,110
There he is!

1556
01:22:20,000 --> 01:22:20,990
Move!

1557
01:22:25,400 --> 01:22:26,435
Left!

1558
01:22:28,760 --> 01:22:30,558
We're heading east on the FDR Drive.

1559
