year of living dangerously

1815
01:36:39,760 --> 01:36:43,071
comes to a close,
in a rare moment of vulnerability,

1816
01:36:43,280 --> 01:36:45,954
I'd like to express a sentiment

1817
01:36:46,040 --> 01:36:47,633
to you about our relationship.

1818
01:36:47,880 --> 01:36:48,915
Okay.

1819
01:36:49,320 --> 01:36:52,790
Well, when I first met you,
I thought you were kind of a

1820
01:36:54,640 --> 01:36:55,630
dick.

1821
01:36:57,160 --> 01:36:58,195
And?

1822
01:37:00,000 --> 01:37:01,638
No, that's it.

1823
01:37:01,880 --> 01:37:02,915
That's very nice.

1824
01:37:03,000 --> 01:37:04,479
- Yeah.
- I'm touched.

1825
01:37:04,640 --> 01:37:06,119
Yeah. Just from the heart.

1826
01:37:06,320 --> 01:37:07,913
Well, I didn't tell you where I was touched.

1827
01:37:08,040 --> 01:37:09,075
You!

1828
01:37:12,680 --> 01:37:14,318
God.
What are we gonna do when this is over?

1829
01:37:14,560 --> 01:37:15,675
We're on our own.

1830
01:37:15,760 --> 01:37:17,398
Our instructions run out after the show.

1831
01:37:18,320 --> 01:37:20,197
Even if there is no "Eye,"

1832
01:37:20,280 --> 01:37:21,998
if we were completely played and we spend

1833
01:37:22,120 --> 01:37:24,111
the next 20 years in jail, then,

1834
01:37:24,680 --> 01:37:26,353
I just want to say that...

1835
01:37:26,600 --> 01:37:28,955
I know. Me, too.

1836
01:37:30,320 --> 01:37:32,231
Little too sentimental for me.

1837
01:37:39,200 --> 01:37:40,270
There they are!

1838
01:37:43,280 --> 01:37:46,033
Go grab 'em! Put 'em down! Go, go, go!

1839
01:37:46,160 --> 01:37:47,150
Grab 'em!

1840
01:37:52,160 --> 01:37:53,195
Get up!

1841
01:37:53,640 --> 01:37:54,835
What the hell?

1842
01:37:58,640 --> 01:37:59,789
Shit!

1843
01:38:09,000 --> 01:38:10,229
Hello, New York!

1844
01:38:18,720 --> 01:38:20,677
Thank you for the magic.

1845
01:38:20,880 --> 01:38:21,950
And thank you for being such

1846
01:38:22,080 --> 01:38:25,072
an incredible and dedicated audience.

1847
01:38:25,480 --> 01:38:27,471
Unfortunately, like all good things,

1848
01:38:27,560 --> 01:38:29,358
it must come to an end.

1849
01:38:32,080 --> 01:38:34,549
So we would like to start our show tonight...

1850
01:38:34,640 --> 01:38:36,199
By saying goodbye.

1851
01:38:37,560 --> 01:38:38,914
All we wanted was to

1852
01:38:39,000 --> 01:38:40,957
bring the world to a magic show.

1853
01:38:41,040 --> 01:38:42,519
And thereby bring a little magic

1854
01:38:42,600 --> 01:38:43,749
back to the world.

1855
01:38:47,760 --> 01:38:48,909
Clear the way!

1856
01:38:58,680 --> 01:39:01,877
This has been
one hell of a ride for all of us.

1857
01:39:02,440 --> 01:39:04,750
But it's time for us to disappear.

1858
01:39:04,920 --> 01:39:06,274
Good night, New York.

1859
01:39:06,520 --> 01:39:07,954
And thank you for believing in us.

1860
01:39:10,600 --> 01:39:11,715
Stop!

1861
01:39:15,240 --> 01:39:16,230
Freeze!

1862
01:39:16,640 --> 01:39:17,835
No!

1863
01:39:35,920 --> 01:39:37,240
God damn it!

1864
01:40:05,840 --> 01:40:07,035
I'm sorry.

1865
01:40:07,720 --> 01:40:09,711
You were right. It's bigger than all of us.

1866
01:40:10,680 --> 01:40:14,753
This is one time I'm not happy being right.

1867
01:40:17,080 --> 01:40:18,718
So I guess this is it.

1868
01:40:20,760 --> 01:40:21,909
Is it?

1869
01:40:48,040 --> 01:40:49,314
Dylan!

1870
01:40:49,720 --> 01:40:52,155
Dylan! Dylan!

1871
01:40:52,240 --> 01:40:53,275
Hey.

1872
01:40:54,640 --> 01:40:56,597
- You see that?
- What?

1873
01:41:00,240 --> 01:41:01,594
Where's the real money?

1874
01:41:17,840 --> 01:41:21,799
You're under arrest! Hands in the air! Now!

1875
01:42:13,000 --> 01:42:14,115
I've been framed.

1876
01:42:15,480 --> 01:42:16,515
I'm sure you were.

1877
01:42:16,600 --> 01:42:17,874
Yeah, but I can prove it.

1878
01:42:18,400 --> 01:42:19,629
I always do.

1879
01:42:20,000 --> 01:42:21,957
Just like I predicted that you'd play the fool.

1880
01:42:22,040 --> 01:42:24,554
Let's just drop the theatricality, all right?

1881
01:42:24,800 --> 01:42:26,950
The cameras aren't rolling in here.

1882
01:42:27,200 --> 01:42:29,669
Fellas, can I have a few minutes
with my friend here alone, please.

1883
01:42:29,760 --> 01:42:31,592
Sure.

1884
01:42:36,560 --> 01:42:37,595
All right.

1885
01:42:38,640 --> 01:42:40,278
I got information to trade.

1886
01:42:40,400 --> 01:42:41,549
I believe that's how it's done.

1887
01:42:41,800 --> 01:42:43,393
If it's of some value.

1888
01:42:45,880 --> 01:42:49,032
These bars give a man time to think.

1889
01:42:50,240 --> 01:42:53,517
And I'm pretty sure I know how they did it.

1890
01:42:53,960 --> 01:42:56,076
Remember the rabbit trick
in the second show?

1891
01:42:57,240 --> 01:42:59,072
The box was never empty.

1892
01:43:01,440 --> 01:43:02,589
The room wasn't either.

1893
01:43:03,880 --> 01:43:06,269
After gaining access to the warehouse,

1894
01:43:06,600 --> 01:43:08,671
The Horsemen left the real safe

1895
01:43:08,760 --> 01:43:11,195
and transformed the whole room

1896
01:43:11,280 --> 01:43:13,749
into a giant rabbit box.

1897
01:43:15,360 --> 01:43:17,510
You go charging in there,

1898
01:43:17,760 --> 01:43:20,195
thinking the safe was already gone.

1899
01:43:20,440 --> 01:43:21,396
Hey!

1900
01:43:21,480 --> 01:43:22,800
Hey! Stop!

1901
01:43:23,000 --> 01:43:24,399
Missing the trick. Again.

1902
01:43:24,480 --> 01:43:25,515
Which was to make you think

1903
01:43:25,800 --> 01:43:27,313
the safe had already been stolen,

1904
01:43:27,400 --> 01:43:29,630
so you'd drop your guard and leave.

1905
01:43:30,200 --> 01:43:33,158
Now, while you were busy
playing with balloon animals,

1906
01:43:33,360 --> 01:43:35,954
someone was breaking into the warehouse.

1907
01:43:54,480 --> 01:43:55,629
Who?

1908
01:43:57,080 --> 01:43:58,559
Jack Wilder.

1909
01:43:59,320 --> 01:44:00,640
Holy shit.

1910
01:44:00,840 --> 01:44:03,229
No. No way. He died
right in front of my eyes.

1911
01:44:04,040 --> 01:44:06,156
Unless, of course, he didn't.

1912
01:44:13,480 --> 01:44:14,754
It's locked.

1913
01:44:15,560 --> 01:44:16,755
Weren't you listening?

1914
01:44:17,240 --> 01:44:18,310
Nothing's ever locked.

1915
01:44:19,720 --> 01:44:22,519
Well done, Mr. Wilder! Good work.

1916
01:44:22,680 --> 01:44:24,512
You're a big boy now, Jack.

1917
01:44:24,680 --> 01:44:27,035
He escaped in a standard FBI vehicle, right?

1918
01:44:30,840 --> 01:44:32,194
Led you to the bridge.

1919
01:44:32,440 --> 01:44:34,033
Where the other Horsemen were waiting

1920
01:44:34,200 --> 01:44:36,077
with an identical replacement car.

1921
01:44:37,080 --> 01:44:38,070
It only took a split second

1922
01:44:38,200 --> 01:44:39,156
for you to lose contact with it

1923
01:44:39,240 --> 01:44:40,230
and make the switch.

1924
01:45:02,560 --> 01:45:05,552
When you crawled into that burning car,

1925
01:45:05,920 --> 01:45:07,911
quite heroically, I might add,

1926
01:45:09,800 --> 01:45:11,871
you almost died trying to rescue

1927
01:45:11,960 --> 01:45:14,952
what I assume was
a cadaver from the morgue.

1928
01:45:16,480 --> 01:45:20,155
Why go through
such an elaborate and dangerous plan

1929
01:45:20,880 --> 01:45:22,393
just to frame one guy?

1930
01:45:22,720 --> 01:45:23,755
I don't know.

1931
01:45:23,920 --> 01:45:25,319
They never kept any of the money they took.

1932
01:45:25,400 --> 01:45:27,835
Yeah, that's the part
I haven't been able to put together yet.

1933
01:45:27,920 --> 01:45:30,594
But I just gave you information that
is substantially more important.

1934
01:45:30,760 --> 01:45:32,433
- No. Not really.
- What?

1935
01:45:32,520 --> 01:45:37,071
I finally got a chance to
really look into Lionel Shrike.

1936
01:45:37,360 --> 01:45:40,113
His comeback attempt. His accident.

1937
01:45:41,080 --> 01:45:44,596
The insurer who denied the family's claim?

1938
01:45:44,800 --> 01:45:45,995
Tressler Insurance.

1939
01:45:47,920 --> 01:45:50,150
The bank that carried the note?

1940
01:45:51,280 --> 01:45:52,918
Credit Republican of Paris.

1941
01:45:53,120 --> 01:45:54,758
Credit Republicain de Paris.

1942
01:45:56,120 --> 01:45:57,519
What do you make of that?

1943
01:45:57,600 --> 01:45:59,750
A sucker is born every minute.

1944
01:46:00,520 --> 01:46:03,114
What if all this was just leading up to

1945
01:46:03,200 --> 01:46:05,919
us getting mugged
in Central Park at 2:00 a.m.?

1946
01:46:06,000 --> 01:46:08,674
No, I'm telling you,
we're right where we need to be.

1947
01:46:08,760 --> 01:46:09,875
We just have to find...

1948
01:46:09,960 --> 01:46:11,075
That?

1949
01:46:13,600 --> 01:46:15,318
The Lionel Shrike tree.

1950
01:46:16,280 --> 01:46:18,794
And the card encased in glass.

1951
01:46:20,120 --> 01:46:21,758
What do we do now?

1952
01:46:38,400 --> 01:46:39,834
Nice!

1953
01:46:55,720 --> 01:46:57,154
So, here's my new theory.

1954
01:46:57,680 --> 01:47:01,071
The legend is that the "Eye" is everywhere.

1955
01:47:01,760 --> 01:47:02,909
Waiting

1956
01:47:03,320 --> 01:47:07,075
for the truly great magicians
to distinguish themselves

1957
01:47:08,040 --> 01:47:09,838
from the mediocre ones.

1958
01:47:10,680 --> 01:47:11,875
Maybe that was you.

1959
01:47:12,520 --> 01:47:14,750
Deep down inside
you wanted nothing more

1960
01:47:14,840 --> 01:47:17,480
than to be part of the "Eye,"
but you were never invited.

1961
01:47:17,560 --> 01:47:20,712
So you try to destroy them.
But instead what happens?

1962
01:47:21,200 --> 01:47:22,679
You pissed them off.

1963
01:47:24,400 --> 01:47:27,438
The Eye isn't real.

1964
01:47:27,520 --> 01:47:30,592
Okay, then, explain then.
Who's behind all this?

1965
01:47:30,880 --> 01:47:32,200
Somebody with an obsession.

1966
01:47:32,440 --> 01:47:33,874
- Meticulous.
- Who?

1967
01:47:33,960 --> 01:47:37,271
Somebody prepared to sacrifice everything.

1968
01:47:37,360 --> 01:47:39,954
Somebody so prepared to lose

1969
01:47:40,040 --> 01:47:42,509
that they wouldn't even be a suspect
until the trick was done.

1970
01:47:42,640 --> 01:47:45,439
I don't want a profile.
I need a name. Who? Who?

1971
01:47:45,560 --> 01:47:47,198
I don't know who.

1972
01:47:47,600 --> 01:47:49,796
But they had to have
access to the warehouse

1973
01:47:49,880 --> 01:47:51,200
to plant the mirrors.

1974
01:47:52,560 --> 01:47:56,394
Always a step ahead of me. And the FBI.

1975
01:47:56,480 --> 01:47:59,711
Got past them not once,
not twice, but consistently.

1976
01:48:00,040 --> 01:48:02,680
Almost as if they were on the...

1977
01:48:15,560 --> 01:48:16,959
The inside.

1978
01:48:29,080 --> 01:48:30,115
You.

1979
01:48:34,760 --> 01:48:35,750
Why?

1980
01:48:36,600 --> 01:48:38,910
That is the question, isn't it?

1981
01:48:39,760 --> 01:48:41,319
You're right.

1982
01:48:41,920 --> 01:48:44,275
I can't tell you how long I've waited

1983
01:48:44,360 --> 01:48:46,317
to see the look on your face.

1984
01:48:48,760 --> 01:48:50,273
Who are you?

1985
01:48:51,360 --> 01:48:52,759
What do you want from me?

1986
01:48:53,600 --> 01:48:55,113
What do I want?

1987
01:48:55,520 --> 01:48:58,433
I want you to spend
the rest of your life in this cell,

1988
01:48:58,520 --> 01:49:02,514
staring at four walls
and wondering how you missed it.

1989
01:49:03,200 --> 01:49:06,272
How you let yourself
be so blinded by your ego

1990
01:49:06,880 --> 01:49:09,269
that you convinced yourself
that you were one step ahead

1991
01:49:09,360 --> 01:49:12,113
when you were always two steps behind.

1992
01:49:16,800 --> 01:49:17,995
Dylan?

1993
01:49:18,960 --> 01:49:19,950
Wait a minute.

1994
01:49:21,000 --> 01:49:23,150
Dylan! How did this happen?

1995
01:49:30,800 --> 01:49:32,473
Dylan!

1996
01:49:32,600 --> 01:49:33,590
Why?

1997
01:49:34,320 --> 01:49:35,310
Why?

1998
01:49:39,320 --> 01:49:41,470
My God.

1999
01:49:42,480 --> 01:49:44,357
I did not see that coming.

2000
01:49:44,480 --> 01:49:45,754
That's impossible!

2001
01:49:45,840 --> 01:49:46,830
No way.

2002
01:49:46,920 --> 01:49:49,309
That was actually pretty good.

2003
01:49:49,760 --> 01:49:50,830
Thank you.

2004
01:49:51,240 --> 01:49:53,470
When I said,
"Always be the smartest guy in the room."

2005
01:49:53,560 --> 01:49:54,595
We were in agreement.

2006
01:49:54,840 --> 01:49:55,989
Okay. Right.

2007
01:49:56,400 --> 01:49:57,390
Henley.

2008
01:49:58,160 --> 01:49:59,992
I've never seen her speechless.

2009
01:50:00,080 --> 01:50:01,673
I take that as a huge compliment.

2010
01:50:02,400 --> 01:50:05,040
Hey, man,
I'm so sorry for kicking your ass. Really.

2011
01:50:05,840 --> 01:50:07,353
Hey, listen, for the record,

2012
01:50:07,520 --> 01:50:11,036
I have always been a 100% believer.

2013
01:50:11,200 --> 01:50:13,430
And the amount of energy
I have expended to keep

2014
01:50:13,520 --> 01:50:15,636
these infidels on point...

2015
01:50:15,720 --> 01:50:17,757
Merritt, you're in.

2016
01:50:18,600 --> 01:50:19,670
God bless.

2017
01:50:19,800 --> 01:50:20,835
Come.

2018
01:50:21,880 --> 01:50:25,032
The real magic is taking
four strong solo acts

2019
01:50:25,240 --> 01:50:27,117
and making them all work together.

2020
01:50:27,360 --> 01:50:29,670
And that's exactly what you did.

2021
01:50:30,640 --> 01:50:31,710
So welcome.

2022
01:50:35,040 --> 01:50:37,077
Welcome to the Eye.

2023
01:51:44,280 --> 01:51:46,351
It was all connected.

2024
01:51:47,000 --> 01:51:49,992
Credit Republican. Tressler Insurance.

2025
01:51:59,360 --> 01:52:00,680
And Elkhorn?

2026
01:52:00,800 --> 01:52:02,711
What's the connection to Shrike?

2027
01:52:05,200 --> 01:52:08,431
Elkhorn started as a safe manufacturer.

2028
01:52:08,760 --> 01:52:10,876
They used cheap steel.

2029
01:52:12,480 --> 01:52:13,754
They cut corners.

2030
01:52:13,840 --> 01:52:17,071
When he got
to the bottom of the river, the safe warped.

2031
01:52:17,160 --> 01:52:18,514
And he was trapped.

2032
01:52:20,080 --> 01:52:21,639
He was your father.

2033
01:52:23,520 --> 01:52:26,876
The morning before the show
didn't feel like any other day.

2034
01:52:27,920 --> 01:52:32,915
When my father said he had to go to work,
he could see that I didn't want him to leave.

2035
01:52:35,160 --> 01:52:40,280
So he gave me his watch, and he told me
to count the seconds until he came back.

2036
01:52:41,480 --> 01:52:44,154
I have never let his watch stop since then.

2037
01:52:44,240 --> 01:52:46,390
And from that moment on,

2038
01:52:46,480 --> 01:52:48,994
I created a persona.

2039
01:52:49,640 --> 01:52:51,551
I planned. I worked out every detail.

2040
01:52:51,640 --> 01:52:54,917
But the one thing
that I couldn't imagine happening

2041
01:52:55,360 --> 01:52:56,509
was you.

2042
01:52:58,200 --> 01:53:01,158
And I know that
the logical conclusion for you

2043
01:53:01,640 --> 01:53:04,393
is to take this case to its resolution.

2044
01:53:04,480 --> 01:53:07,518
And for you to turn me in.

2045
01:53:12,680 --> 01:53:13,715
Yeah.

2046
01:53:15,680 --> 01:53:19,514
But you know how I feel
about resolution and logic.

2047
01:53:20,880 --> 01:53:22,200
And you also know

2048
01:53:23,080 --> 01:53:27,438
that I think some things
are best left unexplained.

2049
01:53:33,920 --> 01:53:35,718
One more secret to lock away.

2050
01:54:03,280 --> 01:54:04,793
Come in close.

2051
01:54:05,280 --> 01:54:06,554
Closer.

2052
01:54:06,640 --> 01:54:08,870
Because now you know our secret.

2053
01:54:08,960 --> 01:54:11,315
We could be anywhere. Watching you.

2054
01:54:11,920 --> 01:54:15,550
We're looking for someone
to help us with our next trick.

2055
01:54:15,640 --> 01:54:18,200
On the count of three, open your eyes

2056
01:54:18,280 --> 01:54:20,237
and tell me what you see.

2057
01:54:21,240 --> 01:54:22,310
One.

2058
01:54:22,440 --> 01:54:23,430
Two...

2059
01:55:55,280 --> 01:55:57,157
Please, stop, stop, stop.

2060
01:55:57,520 --> 01:56:01,229
All right, stop the van. Stop the van.
I'm gonna jump out of the van.

2061
01:56:02,240 --> 01:56:03,719
Thank God.

2062
01:56:05,680 --> 01:56:07,751
Where are we?

2063
01:56:07,840 --> 01:56:10,229
Great, another shit hole.

2064
01:56:10,320 --> 01:56:12,231
Okay, feeling it.

2065
01:56:12,360 --> 01:56:16,513
I'm exhausted, and hungry, and cranky.

2066
01:56:17,560 --> 01:56:19,437
Check out this place.

2067
01:56:19,520 --> 01:56:22,319
- Where'd you bring us?
- Was there no landfill where we were?

2068
01:56:22,400 --> 01:56:24,277
This place is awesome.

2069
01:56:25,800 --> 01:56:26,790
Is this our new gear?

2070
01:56:26,880 --> 01:56:28,439
There'd better not be, like,
matching jumpsuits in there.

2071
01:56:28,520 --> 01:56:29,555
You know I don't wear spandex.

2072
01:56:29,640 --> 01:56:32,029
- It's locked.
- Guys, the cards.

2073
01:56:32,120 --> 01:56:34,634
- What card?
- What do you mean, "what card"?

2074
01:56:38,760 --> 01:56:39,750
Okay.

